Linux:
To compile the project on the development PC execute:
1) autoreconf -i
2) cd build
3) ../configure
4) make

To compile the project for the cross compiler execute:
1) autoreconf -i
2) cd build
3) CC=x86_32-target-linux-gnu-gcc CXX=x86_32-target-linux-gnu-g++ ../configure --prefix=/opt/bt --localstatedir=/var
4) make

To copy the compressed image to the board do:
sshpass -p 'root' scp bt.tgz root@172.16.98.98:/boot/bt/bt.tgz

To run the project execute:
build/outstation

To build debian package:
1) Install devscripts and debhelper packages:
sudo aptitude install devscripts debhelper
2) Create distribution package
cd build
make dist
3) Copy generated distribution file to a directory (e.g. ~/tmp) and unzip
mkdir -p ~/tmp
cp bluetruth-outstation*.tar.gz ~/tmp
cd ~/tmp
tar zxvf bluetruth-outstation*.tar.gz
4) Change directory to bluetruth-outstation*
5) Create debian package
debuild -us -uc
6) The created package can be found in ~/tmp directory

To debug use codelite (outstation.project).


Windows:
To compile the project open outstation.vcproject with Visual Studio 2008.
To create installation file open windows/outstation.iss with Inno Setup Compiler.
